          <msContents>
            <summary><p>A collection of Latin texts by or attributed to Arnaldus de Villanova</p>

<p>[b]Contents[/b]</p>

<p>[b]1.[/b]  f. 1r: Venientia ad ultimum perfectionis et beneuoli/aspectus ad corpus humanum sunt / Ex mineralibus aurum / ... (line 11) Ex corpore humano mumia.</p>

<p>[b]2.[/b]  f. 1v: Manuscript notes.</p>

<p>[b]3.[/b] ff. 2r-56v: Arnaldus de Villanova, [i]De considerationibus operis medicine sive de flebotomia[/i], in Latin.</p>

<p>[b]4.[/b] ff. 57r-66v: Arnaldus de Villanova [?], [i]Aphorismi de ingeniis curativis et preservativis morborum[/i], in Latin.</p>

<p>[b]5.[/b] ff. 67r-84v: Arnaldus de Villanova [?], [i]Aphorismi super libro de ingenio sanitatis[/i], in Latin.</p>

<p>[b]6.[/b] ff. 85r-120r: Arnaldus de Villanova [?], [i]De medicinis simplicibus[/i], in Latin.</p>

<p>[b]7.[/b] ff. 120v-128r: [i]De duabus radicibus secretorum[/i],  a treatise on the properties of Melissa officinalis, i.e. lemon balm, in Latin.</p>
 </summary>
